text: Gooding County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. In the 2020 census, the population was 15,598. Its county seat is Gooding. It is named for Frank R. Gooding, an early 20th Century governor and United States Senator from Idaho. ==Communities== *Bliss *Gooding *Hagerman *Wendell == References == Category:1913 establishments in Idaho
title: Gooding County, Idaho
